Grexor's tips for the Mana Dependant:<br>
<br>
We melee recognize your aversion to physical contact, we really do. Understanding that most of you caster types have never even touched a woman, much less a mob we really do have a desire to keep you safe and comfy, no need to spam us with &quot;TAUNT! GET IT OFF!&quot;<br>
<br>
Building upon this first tenant, please try to steel your nerves when this does happen, running around in circles like a baby chicken does not make my whomping of the mobs ass any easier. Remember, tanks want the mobs attention, you know we are all glory hounds.<br>
<br>
Contrary to popular caster belief, our group chat does have a built in aplifier for your voice. If you whisper, I can hear it at even the greatest distances. When pulling, if you hear a tank say &quot;Will pull till you say you need to med&quot;, feel free to speak up and actually mention when your mana is low and that you need to med. The group system will ensure you don't make your throat hoarse from screaming.<br>
<br>
Shiny things make the caster's eyes sparkle, all too often we tanks see nice messages saying that caster X or cleric Y has looked a corpse while we are still fighting. For added impulse control we suggest groups incorporate a tether and shackle. Its for the caster's own good, all that time wasted looting while were still fighting could have been better spent medding.<br>
<br>
Things that go boom. To help your caster control his fireworks, I suggest tanks give out matches only when the mob is at 25-40%. Casters don't like the attention (beating) that tanks get, after all *they* are the academy educated ones, they deserve the glory, not some meat shield. When given a chance many casters will show off, and get a subsequent beating. We reccomend letting them get the snot beat out of them before saving them, its a good lesson to be learned.<br>
<br>
Be nice to your cleric friends, they need our money, the poor chaps spend lots on gems and things to make you fight better, dont ever be stingy with your cleric.<br>
<br>
<br>
