<br>
A little tip for mages...  If the group doesn't need your damage, undernuke.  A lot.  I've lost count of the sheer amount of times that, instead of using long-cast, high mana cost DDs I've instead sat around and summoned mod rods for the cleric and enchanter, keeping the pulls constant.  After all, what do I really need the mana for, unless they manage to get my pet killed?  hehehe  This works especially well with the rogue pets, since they put out enough extra damage over the norm to keep a mage from needing to nuke heavily in the group environment.<br>
<br>
